Class BasicDoubleLinkedList<T>

java.lang.Object
BasicDoubleLinkedList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Three attributes: head that points to the first node of the list tail that points to the last element of the list size that keeps track of how many elements there are in the link list
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
SortedDoubleLinkedList

  • Method Details

    • addToFront

      public void addToFront(T element)
      Adds to the element front of the list if there are no elements in the list, then head points to a new node and tail else temp will create a new node with element passed in as the data, temp.next will point to head head.prev will point back to temp, and head will point to head.prev which is temp. size is incremented by one.
      Parameters:
      element -

    • addToEnd

      public void addToEnd(T element)
      Adds element to the end of the list. if there is nothing in the list, then a new node is created, which head and tail both point to. else a new node called temp is created and element is passed into the constructor. temp.prev points to tail, tail.next points to temp and tail points back to tail.next which is temp. size is incremented by one
      Parameters:
      element -
